{"title":"protocol.rgp","markdown":{"headingText":"protocol.rgp","headingAttr":{"id":"raccoon.protocol.rgp","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n`protocol.rgp`\n\nRaccoon Game Protocol (RGP) — text-based engine communication.\n\nInspired by UCI (chess). Communication via stdin/stdout.\n\nController -> Engine commands:\n    rgp                     identify protocol\n    isready                 ready check\n    newgame                 start new game\n    position <state_str>    set board position (OpenSpiel state string)\n    dice <d1> <d2>          set dice for next move\n    go simulations <N>      search with N simulations\n    quit                    exit\n\nEngine -> Controller responses:\n    id name Raccoon v0.1\n    rgpok                   protocol acknowledged\n    readyok                 ready\n    bestmove <action>       chosen move (OpenSpiel action index)\n    info score <value> nodes <N>    search info\n\n## Classes\n\n| Name | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| [RGPEngine](#raccoon.protocol.rgp.RGPEngine) | Raccoon Game Protocol engine. |\n\n### RGPEngine { #raccoon.protocol.rgp.RGPEngine }\n\n```python\nprotocol.rgp.RGPEngine(network, default_simulations=100)\n```\n\nRaccoon Game Protocol engine.\n\n#### Methods\n\n| Name | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| [run](#raccoon.protocol.rgp.RGPEngine.run) | Main loop: read commands from stdin, write responses to stdout. |\n\n##### run { #raccoon.protocol.rgp.RGPEngine.run }\n\n```python\nprotocol.rgp.RGPEngine.run(input_stream=None, output_stream=None)\n```\n\nMain loop: read commands from stdin, write responses to stdout.","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":"auto","echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipy